makeFlags="$makeFlags BUILD_LDFLAGS=-Wl,-rpath,/nix/store/fyj9mziyjcii9sc8pnkca4y8kig3gj34-bootstrap-stage0-glibc/lib"
env.preInstall:
if [ -f /nix/store/9m2bwj5gm29r93pxi5bfxki627samnsk-bootstrap-tools/lib/libgcc_s.so.1 ]; then
    mkdir -p $out/lib
    cp /nix/store/9m2bwj5gm29r93pxi5bfxki627samnsk-bootstrap-tools/lib/libgcc_s.so.1 $out/lib/libgcc_s.so.1
    # the .so It used to be a symlink, but now it is a script
    cp -a /nix/store/9m2bwj5gm29r93pxi5bfxki627samnsk-bootstrap-tools/lib/libgcc_s.so $out/lib/libgcc_s.so
fi

env.NIX_HARDENING_ENABLE: fortify stackprotector pic strictoverflow relro bindnow
env.name: binutils-2.31.1
env.preConfigure:
# Clear the default library search path.
if test "$noSysDirs" = "1"; then
    echo 'NATIVE_LIB_DIRS=' >> ld/configure.tgt
fi

# Use symlinks instead of hard links to save space ("strip" in the
# fixup phase strips each hard link separately).
for i in binutils/Makefile.in gas/Makefile.in ld/Makefile.in gold/Makefile.in; do
    sed -i "$i" -e 's|ln |ln -s |'
done

env.name: bootstrap-stage4-stdenv-linux
env.preHook:
# Don't patch #!/interpreter because it leads to retained
# dependencies on the bootstrapTools in the final stdenv.
dontPatchShebangs=1
export NIX_ENFORCE_PURITY="${NIX_ENFORCE_PURITY-1}"
export NIX_ENFORCE_NO_NATIVE="${NIX_ENFORCE_NO_NATIVE-1}"
NIX_LIB64_IN_SELF_RPATH=1

env.NIX_HARDENING_ENABLE: fortify stackprotector pic strictoverflow relro bindnow
env.name: bash-4.4-p23
